article.linkText: Estill leads wounded Wildcats past Wisconsin
article.story: MADISON, Wis. (AP) -- Devin Harris had 28 points, nine assists and seven rebounds in No. 15 Wisconsin's 102-95 exhibition victory over the North Charleston Lowgators on Monday night. Mike Wilkinson scored 18 points and Boo Wade had 15 for Wisconsin, which led by as many as 17 points in the second half. Tierre Brown scored 29 points for North Charleston of the National Basketball Developmental League.
